<h3 id="css">CSS</h3>

<p>Cascading Style Sheets (CSS) are a stylesheet language used to describe the presentation of a document written in HTML or XML (including XML dialects like SVG or XHTML). CSS describes how elements should be rendered on screen, on paper, in speech, or on other media.</p>

<p>Defined using Classes <code class="highlighter-rouge">.name</code> and IDs <code class="highlighter-rouge">#name</code></p>

<p>Classes: more general, used for a group of elements</p>

<p>IDs: more specific, used for single elements</p>

<p><code class="highlighter-rouge">/*comment*/</code></p>

<p><code class="highlighter-rouge">//comment</code></p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-css" data-lang="css"><table class="rouge-table"><tbody><tr><td class="gutter gl"><pre class="lineno">1
